# Real bug found live: building with no .dockerignore at the repo root sent
# an 8.9GB+ (and climbing) build context — every node_modules across every
# workspace package, plus .git history — because the pipeline.ts build stage
# correctly builds with context = repo root (Docker can't otherwise reach
# sibling packages/connectors a Dockerfile COPYs from), but nothing was
# excluding the huge, irrelevant directories from that context.

# Dependencies — reinstalled fresh inside the image via `pnpm install`
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.pnpm-store/

# Build outputs — rebuilt fresh inside the image via `pnpm build`
#
# Confirmed live root cause of a second real bug: Docker's .dockerignore
# matching (unlike .gitignore) does NOT apply a bare pattern like
# "*.tsbuildinfo" at every depth — it only matches at the context root unless
# prefixed with "**/". A leftover packages/agent/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo (and
# packages/types/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo) — untracked, host-local artifacts from
# local `tsc --build` runs — survived into the image, and `tsc --build`
# trusted its "up to date" bookkeeping over the actual (nonexistent, since
# dist/ IS correctly excluded) build output, silently no-op'ing the real
# compile. Every recursive pattern below now has an explicit **/ form.
dist/
**/dist/
.next/
out/
build/
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# VCS
.git/
.github/

# Env files — never bake secrets into an image layer
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Logs
logs/
*.log
**/*.log

# Turbo / test artifacts
.turbo/
**/.turbo/
coverage/
**/coverage/
test-results/
**/test-results/
playwright-report/
**/playwright-report/

# OS / IDE
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/

# Infra — not needed inside app images
infra/
